# Security — pin the @edgecommons scope to GitHub Packages (where @edgecommons/edgecommons is
# published), NEVER the public npm registry. Every @edgecommons/* package in this monorepo is
# workspace-local, so a root/workspace install resolves them through workspace links and never
# contacts a registry at all. This redirect is a fail-closed guard for any install that DOES reach
# a registry — e.g. a standalone `npm install` run inside libs/ts, which cannot see the workspace
# siblings — so @edgecommons/* can never be resolved from public npm, where a dependency-confusion
# squat of @edgecommons/streamlog-node was published. (Pulling the published @edgecommons/edgecommons
# from GitHub Packages standalone additionally needs an auth token; see templates/typescript*/.npmrc.)
@edgecommons:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
